Looking briefly at the data columns, we are can see that there are various numerical and categorical columns¶

The most important column here is y, which is the output variable (desired target): this will tell us if the client subscribed to a term deposit(binary: ‘yes’,’no’).¶

Train-Test Split

20% test data - xtest , ytest - actual target variable

80% train data - xtrain,ytrain

xtrain - i/p features for train data

ytrain - target variable for train data

xtest -i/p features for test data

Inference¶

Through this project, we created a machine learning model that is able to predict how likely clients will subscribe to a bank term deposit. The best model was "Gradiant Boosting Classifier" with Hyperparameter. The model test performance (AUC) is 89 %. The Precision is 69% , recall is 29% & the F1 score is 41%. The important features for this model is "nr.employed", "euribor3m" & "pdays" etc. We should focus on targeting customers with high nr.employed and euribor3m as they are high importance features for the model and business. Therefore, we save time and money knowing the characteristics of clients we should market to and that will lead to increased growth and revenue.
